Book a meeting with Sirish next tuesday.code_output:
from api.provided_api import *
# lowercase names and meeting agenda
list_of_names = ["Sirish"]
list_of_names = [s.lower() for s in list_of_names]

meeting_summary = "Discuss 2023 plans".lower()

# we need to convert the names of the invitees to emails
invitee_emails = name_to_emails(list_of_names)

# get date for meeting
from datetime import datetime, timedelta

today = datetime.now().date()
days_until_tuesday = 2 - today.weekday()
if days_until_tuesday <= 0: # Target day has passed
    days_until_tuesday += 7
next_tuesday = today + timedelta(days_until_tuesday)

# time for meeting
time = timedelta(hours=15)

# duration for meeting
duration = timedelta(hours=1)

# create the meeting
create_event("Discuss 2023 plans", next_tuesday, time, duration, invitee_emails)

# return created meeting
def return_output():
    return get_events(invitee_emails)[-1]

print(return_output())
